74
00:07:33,622 --> 00:07:35,595
Hold it, miss. We
want to talk to you.

75
00:07:35,596 --> 00:07:38,401
Me? I haven't done anything.
You're making a mistake.

76
00:07:38,411 --> 00:07:40,050
I'm a visiting
student from Romania.

77
00:07:40,051 --> 00:07:43,651
- Looks like we got the winning ticket.
- I haven't committed any crime.

78
00:07:43,652 --> 00:07:46,066
- We just want to take you back to the Farraday Clinic.
- No! No!

79
00:07:46,067 --> 00:07:48,471
- Aura Petrescu, come on.
- No. No, please.

80
00:07:48,472 --> 00:07:51,276
Don't take me back,
I got lots of money.

81
00:07:51,277 --> 00:07:53,280
I can give you thousands
of dollars. Please!

82
00:07:53,281 --> 00:07:55,285
Don't worry. We're not
gonna take you back.

83
00:07:55,295 --> 00:07:58,441
- The law says we gotta bring you to your parents.
- We'll take you to the clinic.

84
00:07:58,442 --> 00:08:01,638
No! No!

85
00:08:01,648 --> 00:08:04,723
- We have to take you to your parents.
- No! Fuck you!

86
00:08:04,724 --> 00:08:07,158
You can't do that!

87
00:08:07,159 --> 00:08:09,132
Break it up. Everything's
under control.

88
00:08:09,133 --> 00:08:12,610
<i>Break it up, guys.
Let's move on.</i>

89
00:08:21,307 --> 00:08:23,321
Little bitch.

90
00:08:27,049 --> 00:08:29,523
Home sweet home, huh?

91
00:08:43,171 --> 00:08:45,174
<i>Yes, what do you want?</i>

92
00:08:45,175 --> 00:08:47,579
Good afternoon, we're from
Metro youth services.

93
00:08:47,580 --> 00:08:49,953
<i>- Yes?
- We have aura.</i>

94
00:08:49,954 --> 00:08:52,398
<i>Aura? You have aura?</i>

95
00:08:52,399 --> 00:08:54,463
Aura!

96
00:08:54,473 --> 00:08:57,779
Oh, my poor little baby!

97
00:08:57,780 --> 00:09:00,515
I am the mother
of this difficult

98
00:09:00,516 --> 00:09:04,132
but very beautiful little girl.

99
00:09:04,133 --> 00:09:07,739
My thanks to both you gentlemen
for bringing my baby back home.

100
00:09:07,740 --> 00:09:10,144
<i>Very kind, thank you.</i>

101
00:09:14,063 --> 00:09:17,198
It's for your own good that
we put you in the clinic.

102
00:09:17,199 --> 00:09:19,673
That's where you stay...
You understand?

103
00:09:19,674 --> 00:09:21,678
...Until <i>we decide.</i>

104
00:09:21,688 --> 00:09:24,092
Mamica, I hate the cell.

105
00:09:24,093 --> 00:09:26,867
Please don't make me
go back. I'll die.

106
00:09:29,043 --> 00:09:31,246
Look who's come back to us.

107
00:09:31,247 --> 00:09:33,250
Two policeman brought her home.

108
00:09:36,057 --> 00:09:38,061
What a surprise.

109
00:09:38,071 --> 00:09:40,881
Always
making trouble for your mother.

110
00:09:40,882 --> 00:09:44,082
I'm sorry, Tata, but they're
horrible at the clinic.

111
00:09:44,083 --> 00:09:46,486
They're trying to kill me.

112
00:09:46,487 --> 00:09:49,302
Take her upstairs.

113
00:09:49,303 --> 00:09:51,307
Bring her some tea.

114
00:10:01,838 --> 00:10:04,674
This is too much.
Your mother's very angry.

115
00:10:04,684 --> 00:10:07,959
- I know, Tata, but please let me stay...
- aura, enough.

116
00:10:07,960 --> 00:10:11,177
- I swear I'll be better.
- Your mother has a lot to think about.

117
00:10:11,178 --> 00:10:13,842
- Another seance?
- A big one.

118
00:10:16,517 --> 00:10:19,322
I'll bring you
some dinner later, huh?

119
00:10:19,323 --> 00:10:21,326
Try to eat.

120
00:10:21,327 --> 00:10:23,731
- Make your mother happy.
- I'm not hungry.

121
00:10:23,732 --> 00:10:25,736
Aura... you have to eat.

122
00:10:25,746 --> 00:10:28,562
- No.
- That's why you're going back to the clinic.

123
00:10:28,563 --> 00:10:32,529
No. No!

124
00:10:41,487 --> 00:10:43,632
Good evening!

125
00:11:01,187 --> 00:11:05,530
- Hello.
- So good to see you. Let me take your umbrella.

126
00:11:05,531 --> 00:11:09,071
It's a foul night, Stefan, but
maybe the spirits will like it.

127
00:11:09,072 --> 00:11:11,376
She's very good.

128
00:11:11,377 --> 00:11:16,958
When Nicolas starts talking...
Watch my hands.

129
00:11:18,832 --> 00:11:21,537
- I'm the one who telephoned.
- Ah!

130
00:11:23,882 --> 00:11:25,816
Oh my god.

131
00:11:54,273 --> 00:11:56,517
Am I late?

132
00:12:30,615 --> 00:12:32,619
Aura?

133
00:12:49,503 --> 00:12:51,507
Where's George?

134
00:12:51,517 --> 00:12:53,531
Will we be able
to contact my mother?

135
00:12:53,532 --> 00:12:57,198
- Shh!
- We have so many questions.

136
00:12:57,199 --> 00:13:00,004
<i>We, who are gathered here.</i>

137
00:13:01,848 --> 00:13:03,550
Nicolas...

138
00:13:03,551 --> 00:13:05,155
My precious...

139
00:13:07,159 --> 00:13:08,762
Will you help us?

140
00:13:13,942 --> 00:13:16,146
<i>Nicolas...</i>

141
00:13:16,156 --> 00:13:18,631
<i>Are you here with us tonight?</i>

142
00:13:23,040 --> 00:13:25,074
<i>I am searching for you.</i>

143
00:13:28,762 --> 00:13:31,967
Let... me...

144
00:13:31,968 --> 00:13:35,144
In!

145
00:13:40,495 --> 00:13:43,069
This is not Nicolas.

146
00:13:43,070 --> 00:13:46,576
<i>Some other soul
is here with us tonight,</i>

147
00:13:46,577 --> 00:13:48,912
trying to break though.

148
00:13:51,056 --> 00:13:55,504
<i>Some... some soul.</i>

149
00:13:55,505 --> 00:13:59,582
One of... Those who follow...

150
00:13:59,583 --> 00:14:01,456
The recent dead,

151
00:14:01,457 --> 00:14:04,031
who followed their killers.

152
00:14:04,032 --> 00:14:07,238
Speak!

153
00:14:07,239 --> 00:14:09,643
- My head.
<i>- My head.</i>

154
00:14:11,718 --> 00:14:15,995
- Took my head.
- <i>Took my head.</i>

155
00:14:17,870 --> 00:14:21,747
- Murdered me!
- <i>Murdered me!</i>

156
00:14:21,748 --> 00:14:25,655
A monster with a noose.

157
00:14:27,599 --> 00:14:30,875
I wasn't the first,

158
00:14:30,876 --> 00:14:34,883
and I won't be the last.

159
00:14:37,499 --> 00:14:41,537
I know who the killer is!

160
00:14:44,754 --> 00:14:48,361
I'm the only one who knows!

161
00:14:49,563 --> 00:14:53,070
The killer is present!

162
00:14:58,020 --> 00:15:01,666
- Don't break the chain!
- <i>Don't move!</i>

163
00:15:01,667 --> 00:15:03,640
I see you!

164
00:15:03,641 --> 00:15:06,917
<i>You can't hide from me!</i>

165
00:15:06,918 --> 00:15:09,692
<i>I know you!</i>

166
00:15:14,102 --> 00:15:16,346
Mama!

167
00:15:16,347 --> 00:15:18,882
<i>Mama!</i>

168
00:15:18,892 --> 00:15:20,254
Mama!

169
00:15:20,255 --> 00:15:23,630
Tata! Stop!

170
00:15:23,631 --> 00:15:25,605
<i>Stop!</i>

171
00:15:30,485 --> 00:15:32,860
Papa!

172
00:16:02,319 --> 00:16:03,922
<i>Aura!</i>

173
00:16:23,250 --> 00:16:25,425
Dad! Mama!

174
00:16:45,545 --> 00:16:48,891
What did you see?
You've got to tell me!

175
00:16:48,892 --> 00:16:50,764
You must have seen something!

176
00:16:50,765 --> 00:16:52,798
Who was it?

177
00:16:52,799 --> 00:16:54,673
I... I didn't see anything.

178
00:16:55,715 --> 00:16:57,919
He had... he had

179
00:16:57,920 --> 00:17:00,224
their heads
in front of his face.

180
00:17:03,801 --> 00:17:06,576
Check these weird
things out on the wall.

181
00:17:06,577 --> 00:17:08,581
They may be something
from the occult.

182
00:17:09,783 --> 00:17:13,060
It is getting late.
Take me home.

183
00:17:16,176 --> 00:17:20,053
There was something wrong tonight from the
beginning. I could feel it in the room.

184
00:17:20,054 --> 00:17:22,268
So neither of you
heard anything?

185
00:17:35,294 --> 00:17:38,139
Did she have any other
relatives besides her parents?

186
00:17:38,140 --> 00:17:39,503
No one.

187
00:17:39,513 --> 00:17:43,450
<i>You know, captain,
until her recent escape,</i>

188
00:17:43,451 --> 00:17:45,454
<i>sh... she was under my care.</i>

189
00:17:45,455 --> 00:17:48,129
- Is that so?
- <i>She was a patient of mine</i>

190
00:17:48,130 --> 00:17:50,404
at the Farraday Clinic.

191
00:17:50,405 --> 00:17:53,881
- It was her parents' wish.
- What was wrong with her?

192
00:17:53,882 --> 00:17:56,556
I'm afraid I'm not
at Liberty to say, captain.

193
00:17:56,557 --> 00:17:59,964
<i>But it has nothing
to do with this case.</i>

194
00:17:59,974 --> 00:18:01,787
We're prepared to take her back.

195
00:18:01,788 --> 00:18:04,913
<i>Sh... she needs our help.</i>

196
00:18:04,914 --> 00:18:09,061
Well, tomorrow you go downtown and
file papers with youth services.

197
00:18:09,062 --> 00:18:11,005
<i>I'm sure they'll
hand her over to you</i>

198
00:18:11,006 --> 00:18:13,611
after we're done
questioning her.

199
00:18:21,467 --> 00:18:25,544
A bizarre double-murder brings
a madman's total to four.

200
00:18:25,545 --> 00:18:28,349
Striking steel workers go
back to the bargaining table.

201
00:18:28,350 --> 00:18:32,429
<i>Warm weather price-hikes put
a dent in your pocketbook.</i>

202
00:18:32,439 --> 00:18:34,848
Sounds like you could have
some fun with that one.

203
00:18:34,849 --> 00:18:37,247
They say they're calling
him "the headhunter."

204
00:18:37,248 --> 00:18:40,053
So I've heard.

205
00:18:40,054 --> 00:18:42,257
I suppose grace told you, huh?

206
00:18:42,258 --> 00:18:44,271
Yeah, we communicate
now and then.

207
00:18:44,272 --> 00:18:47,077
I suppose she told you
what the guy looks like?

208
00:18:47,078 --> 00:18:49,081
Don't worry about it,
nobody saw you, mark.

209
00:18:49,082 --> 00:18:52,689
Oh, very funny!
You're a laugh-riot.

210
00:18:52,699 --> 00:18:55,916
Now could we do some actual
work around here, please?

211
00:18:55,917 --> 00:18:57,838
Arnie, what are you doing?

212
00:18:57,839 --> 00:18:59,843
Besides putting on pounds.

213
00:18:59,853 --> 00:19:01,816
Ha-ha. We've got a, uh...

214
00:19:01,817 --> 00:19:05,363
Leading composite using
last night's KKK rally...

215
00:19:05,364 --> 00:19:08,510
- - <i>...And
the space shuttle landing</i>

216
00:19:08,511 --> 00:19:11,646
and the president's
trip to Belgrade

217
00:19:11,647 --> 00:19:14,592
hmm. Any sex?

218
00:19:14,593 --> 00:19:16,997
Hmm. Probably. The first
lady's not going.

219
00:19:16,998 --> 00:19:18,600
Forget it. I think there was sex

